issue.title: prevent skip on previous action
issue.body:
Hello,

I wanted to add behavior such as not skipping when I hit the previous key.

I made a try: the next action ( shortcuts and buttons ) are catched and a message is sent to the background script, which then sets a `doNotSkipNext` flag.

Problem is, the message is received after the url change event.

I will try to figure out another way to achieve that.

I personnaly prefer this behavior, do you think it could be useful to have it as option ?

issue.title: Delete old history entries if it becomes too large for localStorage
issue.body:
It would be optimal to clear the oldest entries. I save each history entry as

```
{
  image-id: Date // the time this id was saved at with Date.now()
}
```

You can use wrap calls to localStorage.setItem with `try...catch` blocks to check for quota exceeded errors. http://chrisberkhout.com/blog/localstorage-errors/

issue.title: Enabling skipping shouldn't start skipping the current image
issue.body: It's a little annoying that enabling skipping makes you start skipping right away. I think it'll be better to only skip after you move on to the next image after you enable skipping. Making this change will help #17 work better as well.

issue.title: Keyboard shortcuts
issue.body:
Added skip and store toggling. 'z' will toggle skip, 'x' will toggle
storing. Holding shift will also toggle skip until released.

issue.title: Check for and avoid extra params when storing image ID
issue.body: If you're on a page to check comments, there are extra params in the URL. "gallery/image-id?extra" Check for the "?" and avoid adding those extra params as the stored image ID.

issue.title: handle processing the id in the url when params are present
issue.body:
Now the id is parsed from the url more accurately. This handles the case when there are params in the url.

There's also another quick fix for searching for the "://imgur.com" url like mentioned in #8.
